### 1.2 Basic Differentiation Rules

#### Additional Questions

1. Differentiate. a) \(y=5\) b) \(y=3x\) c) \(f(x)=x^{3}\) d) \(f(x)=x^{7}\) e) \(g(x)=-x^{-1}\) f) \(g(x)=x^{-3}\) g) \(y=\frac{1}{x^{12}}\) h) \(f(x)=x^{n-1}\)
2. Differentiate. a) \(y=9x^{2}\) b) \(y=12x^{0.25}\) c) \(f(x)=-2x^{3}\) d) \(f(x)=5x^{\frac{1}{5}}\) e) \(g(x)=\frac{2}{\sqrt{x}}\) f) \(g(x)=2(3x)^{2}\) g) \(y=\left(\frac{2}{x^{3}}\right)^{2}\) h) \(f(x)=(9x^{\frac{1}{2}})^{\frac{1}{2}}\)
3. Differentiate. a) \(f(x)=3x-x^{2}\) b) \(y=3x^{4}+2x^{3}\) c) \(y=7x^{3}-3x^{2}+5x\)d) \(f(x)=x^{-2}+x^{2}+2x\) e) \(f(x)=(2x+1)^{2}\) f) \(g(x)=(x+1)(x-1)\) g) \(g(x)=x^{2}(2x-3)\) h) \(g(x)=mx^{n-1}\)
4. Find the slope of the tangent to the graph of the given function at the point whose \(x\)-coordinate is given. a) \(f(x)=2x^{3}\), \(x=1\) b) \(f(x)=\frac{1}{3}x^{-3}\), \(x=-1\) c) \(g(x)=3x^{2}-5x\), \(x=2\) d) \(g(x)=18x^{\frac{1}{3}}\), \(x=9\) e) \(h(x)=\frac{5x^{4}-4x}{2x^{2}}\), \(x=1\) f) \(h(x)=(2-x)^{2}\), \(x=-2\)
5. Find an equation of the tangent to the curve at the given point. a) \(y=x^{2}+3\), (-2, 7) b) \(y=3x^{2}-x+1\), (1, 3) c) \(y=\frac{15}{2x^{2}}\), \(\left(3,\frac{5}{6}\right)\) d) \(y=\frac{4x-3x^{4}}{2x^{2}}\), \(\left(1,\frac{1}{2}\right)\) e) \(y=(2x+3)^{2}\), (-1, 1) f) \(y=\frac{4}{(\sqrt{2x})^{3}}\), \(\left(2,\frac{1}{2}\right)\)
6. Consider the parabola \(y=x^{2}-6x+5\). a) At what point on the parabola is the slope of the tangent equal to zero? b) Find the vertex of the parabola by completing the square. c) How can the vertex of a parabola be found without completing the square? Test your hypothesis on the following parabolas. i) \(y=x^{2}-6x+12\) ii) \(y=x^{2}+9x-2\) iii) \(y=x^{2}+2x+5\) d) Will your method work for all parabolas? Explain.
7. Find the equations of both lines that pass through (4, -10) and are tangent to the parabola \(y=x^{2}\) - 10x + 18.
8. The tangent to the curve \(y=x^{2}\) at the point (1, 1) intersects the curve at another point A. a) Find the equation of the tangent to the curve at (1, 1). b) Find the coordinates of A. c) Find the equation of the tangent at A.